463/*%
464 * Attributes for statistics counters of RRset and Rdatatype types.
465 *
466 * _OTHERTYPE
467 * The rdata type is not explicitly supported and the corresponding counter
468 * is counted for other such types, too. When this attribute is set,
469 * the base type is of no use.
470 *
471 * _NXRRSET
472 * RRset type counters only. Indicates the RRset is non existent.
473 *
474 * _NXDOMAIN
475 * RRset type counters only. Indicates a non existent name. When this
476 * attribute is set, the base type is of no use.
477 *
478 * _STALE
479 * RRset type counters only. This indicates a record that marked for
480 * removal.
481 *
482 * Note: incrementing _STALE will decrement the corresponding non-stale
483 * counter.
484 */
485#define DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_ATTR_OTHERTYPE 0x0001
486#define DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_ATTR_NXRRSET 0x0002
487#define DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_ATTR_NXDOMAIN 0x0004
488#define DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_ATTR_STALE 0x0008
489
490/*%<
491 * Conversion macros among dns_rdatatype_t, attributes and isc_statscounter_t.
492 */
493#define DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_BASE(type) ((dns_rdatatype_t)((type) & 0xFFFF))
494#define DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_ATTR(type) ((type) >> 16)
495#define DNS_RDATASTATSTYPE_VALUE(b, a) (((a) << 16) | (b))
496
497/*%<
498 * Types of dump callbacks.
499 */
500typedef void (*dns_generalstats_dumper_t)(isc_statscounter_t, uint64_t,
501 void *);
502typedef void (*dns_rdatatypestats_dumper_t)(dns_rdatastatstype_t, uint64_t,
503 void *);
504typedef void (*dns_opcodestats_dumper_t)(dns_opcode_t, uint64_t, void *);
505
506typedef void (*dns_rcodestats_dumper_t)(dns_rcode_t, uint64_t, void *);

510isc_result_t
511dns_generalstats_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_stats_t **statsp, int ncounters);
512/*%<
513 * Create a statistics counter structure of general type. It counts a general
514 * set of counters indexed by an ID between 0 and ncounters -1.
515 * This function is obsolete. A more general function, isc_stats_create(),
516 * should be used.
517 *
518 * Requires:
519 *\li 'mctx' must be a valid memory context.
520 *
521 *\li 'statsp' != NULL && '*statsp' == NULL.
522 *
523 * Returns:
524 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS -- all ok
525 *
526 *\li anything else -- failure
527 */
528
529isc_result_t
530dns_rdatatypestats_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_stats_t **statsp);
531/*%<
532 * Create a statistics counter structure per rdatatype.
